2. Create an empty string called "reversed_string".

3. Use a loop to iterate through each character in the original string, starting from the last character.

4. For each character, add it to the "reversed_string" variable.

5. After all characters have been added, return the "reversed_string".

6. Example function:

```
function reverse_string(str) {

  let reversed_string = "";

  for (let i = str.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    reversed_string += str[i];
  }

  return reversed_string;
}
```

7. Call the function with a test string to check if it works:

```
console.log(reverse_string("hello world")); // "dlrow olleh"
```

